uthorized\\\", message: \\\"User not found.\\\" },\\n-58:   }\\n+58:         { status: 401 }\\n-59: }\\n+59:       );\\n-60: \\n+60:     }\\n+61: \\n+62:     if (isInactive) {\\n+63:       return NextResponse.json(\\n+64:         { success: false, error: \\\"Forbidden\\\", message: \\\"This account is inactive.\\\" },\\n+65:         { status: 403 }\\n+66:       );\\n+67:     }\\n+68: \\n+69:     return NextResponse.json(\\n+70:       {\\n+71:         success: true,\\n+72:         user: userResponse,\\n+73:       },\\n+74:       { status: 200 }\\n+75:     );\\n+76:   } catch (error: any) {\\n+77:     console.error(\\\"Auth me error:\\\", error);\\n+78:     return NextResponse.json(\\n+79:       { success: false, error: \\\"Internal Server Error\\\", message: \\\"An unexpected error occurred.\\\" },\\n+80:       { status: 500 }\\n+81:     );\\n+82:   }\\n+83: }\\n+84: \\n+85: \\n```\",\"success\":true},\"durationMs\":4}}\n./automation/logs/2026-06-27T21-14-20-109Z-175-phase6-auth-users-dynamodb-implement.log:411:{\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T21:14:08.315Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_start\",\"contentType\":\"tool\",\"toolName\":\"run_commands\",\"toolCallId\":\"biod3dok\",\"input\":{\"commands\":[\"npx eslint lib/dynamodb-client.ts app/api/v1/auth/login/route.ts app/api/v1/auth/me/route.ts\"]}}}\n./automation/logs/2026-06-27T21-14-20-109Z-175-phase6-auth-users-dynamodb-implement.log:412:{\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T21:14:11.181Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_end\",\"contentType\":\"tool\",\"toolName\":\"run_commands\",\"toolCallId\":\"biod3dok\",\"output\":[{\"query\":\"npx eslint lib/dynamodb-client.ts app/api/v1/auth/login/route.ts app/api/v1/auth/me/route.ts\",\"result\":\"\",\"success\":true}],\"durationMs\":2866}}\n./automation/logs/2026-06-27T21-14-20-109Z-175-phase6-auth-users-dynamodb-implement.log:416:{\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T21:14:16.803Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_start\",\"contentType\":\"reasoning\",\"reasoning\":\"**Mapping Secure Data Structures**\\n\\nI'm now deeply engrossed in mapping out a DynamoDB table (`GFF_USERS`) to replace the memory stores. I'm focusing on a secure, scalable single-table design, and I'm really excited about showing clear role-based permissions and client isolation. This all comes to life as `gff_admin`, `client_admin`, and `client_member` entries. I'm taking special care to ensure the backend logic change is non-intrusive and doesn't affect the UI at all. This means my changes are focused on specific files: `lib/dynamodb-client.ts`, `app/api/v1/auth/login/route.ts`, and `app/api/v1/auth/me/route.ts`. The rest remain untouched. I'm also ensuring the JWT behavior from phase 5 stays the same.\\n\\n\\n\",\"redacted\":false}}\n./automation/logs/2026-06-27T21-14-20-109Z-175-phase6-auth-users-dynamodb-implement.log:422:{\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T21:14:19.471Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_end\",\"contentType\":\"reasoning\",\"reasoning\":\"**Reviewing Initial Code Condition**\\n\\nI'm thrilled; the code passed linting with flying colors! Now, I'm shifting focus to a quick self-review, scrutinizing the design and implementation plan, especially regarding the user authentication narrative. I want to make sure we're on track with the planned modernization efforts.\\n\\n\\n**Mapping Secure Data Structures**\\n\\nI'm now deeply engrossed in mapping out a DynamoDB table (`GFF_USERS`) to replace the memory stores. I'm focusing on a secure, scalable single-table design, and I'm really excited about showing clear role-based permissions and client isolation. This all comes to life as `gff_admin`, `client_admin`, and `client_member` entries. I'm taking special care to ensure the backend logic change is non-intrusive and doesn't affect the UI at all. This means my changes are focused on specific files: `lib/dynamodb-client.ts`, `app/api/v1/auth/login/route.ts`, and `app/api/v1/auth/me/route.ts`. The rest remain untouched. I'm also ensuring the JWT behavior from phase 5 stays the same.\\n\\n\\n\"}}\n./automation/logs/2026-06-27T21-14-20-109Z-175-phase6-auth-users-dynamodb-implement.log:423:{\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T21:14:19.475Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_start\",\"contentType\":\"tool\",\"toolName\":\"submit_and_exit\",\"toolCallId\":\"yneq3w6m\",\"input\":{\"summary\":\"Successfully completed the move of authentication users to DynamoDB (Phase 6 Auth).\\n\\n1. Installed `@aws-sdk/client-dynamodb` and `@aws-sdk/lib-dynamodb` to provide AWS DynamoDB connectivity in our TypeScript Next.js API endpoints.\\n2. Installed `bcryptjs` and `@types/bcryptjs` to handle bcrypt secure password hashing and verification in TypeScript.\\n3. Created `lib/dynamodb-client.ts` to construct a robust DynamoDB client connection. It fetches items from the `GFF_USERS` DynamoDB table, verifies password_hash (bcrypt) or local plain-text/SHA-256 fallback passwords, and maps roles ('gff_admin', 'client_admin', 'client_member') to correct clearances, client associations, and permissions.\\n4. Updated `app/api/v1/auth/login/route.ts` to first query DynamoDB for user lookup and password verification, falling back gracefully to `API_MOCK_USERS` memory object if not found or if credentials are not configured.\\n5. Updated `app/api/v1/auth/me/route.ts` to fetch the currently authenticated user details from DynamoDB first, falling back to mock users.\\n6. Ran backend verification tests (`npm run backend:check`), local API test scripts (`node scripts/verify-auth-endpoints.js` and `node scripts/test-user-apis.js`), and checked code style via ESLint—all tests passed flawlessly with zero errors.\",\"verified\":true}}}\n./automation/logs/2026-06-27T21-14-20-109Z-175-phase6-auth-users-dynamodb-implement.log:424:{\"ts\":\"2026-06-27T21:14:19.485Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_end\",\"contentType\":\"tool\",\"toolName\":\"submit_and_exit\",\"toolCallId\":\"yneq3w6m\",\"outp